, Takim investigates the Shi›ite self-understanding of authority and argues that this was an important factor in the formation of a distinct Shi›ite leadership. The Heirs of the Prophet also provides a new understanding of textual authority in Islam by examining authority construction and the struggle for legitimacy evidenced in Islamic biographical dictionaries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthorityxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aCharisma (Personality trait)xReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aShī??ahxGovernment. 0aTemporal power of religious rulers. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Islam. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Shi'a.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791481912423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791481912/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles